-- 6. Tunbridge Wells × Social Media Setup
INSERT INTO public.local_content (service_slug, town_slug, intro_paragraph, local_context, competition_landscape, success_approach, local_stats, pain_points, solutions, faqs, layout_variant)
VALUES (
  'social-media-setup',
  'tunbridge-wells',
  'Tunbridge Wells has a vibrant online community that increasingly shapes purchasing decisions. Local Facebook groups buzz with recommendation requests. Instagram drives discovery for the town''s independent food scene and boutique retail. LinkedIn connects the professional services sector with the commuter and business community. A family considering a restaurant on Chapel Place checks Instagram before booking. A homeowner near Calverley Park asks for a decorator recommendation in a Tunbridge Wells Facebook group. A business owner seeking an accountant reviews LinkedIn profiles before making contact. Yet many Tunbridge Wells businesses have social media presences that were set up hastily, have not been updated in months, or present an inconsistent image that undermines the quality they actually deliver. We set up and optimise social media profiles for Tunbridge Wells businesses that look professional, appear in the right conversations, and convert social browsers into paying customers.',
  'Tunbridge Wells'' social media landscape is shaped by its independent, culturally engaged demographic. Instagram is particularly strong in this market, with The Pantiles, Chapel Place food scene, Calverley Grounds, and the High Weald backdrop providing photogenic content hooks that few Kent towns can match. Facebook community groups are active with recommendation requests and local discussion. LinkedIn connects the professional services and business community. The Assembly Hall Theatre, Trinity Theatre, and regular Pantiles events provide ongoing content opportunities. The food and artisan culture generates organic social sharing that well-positioned businesses can leverage.',
  'Social media quality among Tunbridge Wells businesses is varied. The independent food and retail scene on The Pantiles and Chapel Place tends to maintain active, visually strong Instagram presences. Professional services and trades are far less consistent, with many having outdated or dormant profiles. In a market where the demographic actively checks social media before making purchasing decisions, this gap between visual businesses and service businesses is commercially significant.',
  'Our social media setup for Tunbridge Wells identifies the platforms that drive business for your specific sector. Instagram for the food, retail, and lifestyle businesses leveraging The Pantiles and Chapel Place backdrop. Facebook for community engagement and recommendation visibility across the borough. LinkedIn for professional services targeting the business and commuter demographic. Each platform is set up with professional imagery, consistent branding, and a content framework that maintains quality after our handover.',
  '{"population": 60000, "borough": "Tunbridge Wells", "business_districts": ["The Pantiles", "High Street", "Chapel Place", "Mount Pleasant", "Camden Road"], "key_fact": "Visually rich town with strong Instagram culture and active Facebook community groups"}',
  '[{"title": "Invisible in Tunbridge Wells community group recommendations", "description": "When a Tunbridge Wells resident asks for a plumber recommendation in a Facebook group, the businesses that get tagged are those with professional, active profiles. If your page is outdated or nonexistent, you are excluded from the most powerful word-of-mouth channel in the borough."}, {"title": "Outdated social profiles undermining Tunbridge Wells business trust", "description": "A prospect checks your Facebook or Instagram after hearing about your business. They find a blurry profile picture, last post from four months ago, and outdated information. Trust evaporates. They choose the competitor whose social presence looks current and professional. In a town that values aesthetics, dormant profiles are particularly damaging."}, {"title": "Wrong platform focus wasting Tunbridge Wells marketing effort", "description": "A professional service firm posting daily on Instagram while neglecting LinkedIn misses the business audience entirely. A Pantiles restaurant investing in LinkedIn while ignoring Instagram misses the food-discovery audience that drives bookings. Platform selection matters as much as content quality in Tunbridge Wells."}]',
  '[{"title": "Platform-specific setup for Tunbridge Wells market segments", "description": "We identify which platforms matter for your specific Tunbridge Wells audience and set up each one professionally. Instagram for food, retail, and lifestyle businesses leveraging the town''s photogenic character. Facebook for community visibility and recommendations. LinkedIn for professional services. Every platform optimised for its intended audience."}, {"title": "Professional visual identity across Tunbridge Wells social profiles", "description": "Consistent, high-quality cover images, profile photos, and branded templates across every platform. Your social presence reflects the same visual quality as your Pantiles signage or Chapel Place shopfront. Tunbridge Wells customers encounter a cohesive, trustworthy brand image wherever they find you."}, {"title": "Content framework using Tunbridge Wells events and local hooks", "description": "A practical content calendar using Pantiles events, Assembly Hall Theatre programming, seasonal changes in Calverley Grounds and Dunorlan Park, and the town''s food scene as content hooks. Your team can maintain engaging, locally relevant social media independently using the framework and templates we provide."}]',
  '[{"question": "Which social platforms matter most for Tunbridge Wells businesses?", "answer": "Instagram is exceptionally strong in Tunbridge Wells due to the town''s visual character and food culture. Facebook is essential for community engagement and recommendations. LinkedIn is critical for professional services. We recommend the right mix based on your specific audience and sector."}, {"question": "Can you help me get noticed in Tunbridge Wells Facebook groups?", "answer": "We set up your profile to make a strong impression when you are tagged or mentioned in community groups. Professional imagery, complete information, and active posting history all contribute to credibility in group recommendations. We also provide guidelines for authentic community group engagement."}, {"question": "How long does social media setup take?", "answer": "A complete multi-platform setup typically takes one to two weeks. This includes platform strategy, professional visual asset creation, profile optimisation with accurate business information, and development of a content framework with templates for ongoing management."}, {"question": "Do you provide ongoing social media management?", "answer": "Our core service is professional setup and strategy. We deliver optimised profiles with content frameworks that your team can execute independently. Ongoing management retainers are available if needed, but many Tunbridge Wells businesses find the framework and templates sufficient to maintain quality."}]',
  'trust'
)
